{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"If you are a blind child in India,"},{"time":4000,"text":"you will very likely have to contend with"},{"time":7000,"text":"at least two big pieces of bad news."},{"time":10000,"text":"The first bad news"},{"time":12000,"text":"is that the chances of getting treatment"},{"time":15000,"text":"are extremely slim to none,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and that's because most of the blindness"},{"time":20000,"text":"alleviation programs in the country"},{"time":22000,"text":"are focused on adults,"},{"time":24000,"text":"and there are very, very few hospitals"},{"time":27000,"text":"that are actually equipped to treat children."},{"time":31000,"text":"In fact, if you were to be treated,"},{"time":36000,"text":"you might well end up being treated"},{"time":39000,"text":"by a person who has no medical credentials"},{"time":42000,"text":"as this case from Rajasthan illustrates."},{"time":45000,"text":"This is a three-year-old orphan girl"},{"time":47000,"text":"who had cataracts."},{"time":49000,"text":"So, her caretakers took her"},{"time":51000,"text":"to the village medicine man,"},{"time":53000,"text":"and instead of suggesting to the caretakers"},{"time":56000,"text":"that the girl be taken to a hospital,"},{"time":59000,"text":"the person decided to burn her abdomen"},{"time":61000,"text":"with red-hot iron bars"},{"time":63000,"text":"to drive out the demons."},{"time":65000,"text":"The second piece of bad news"},{"time":68000,"text":"will be delivered to you"},{"time":70000,"text":"by neuroscientists, who will tell you"},{"time":73000,"text":"that if you are older than four or five years of age,"},{"time":76000,"text":"that even if you have your eye corrected,"},{"time":79000,"text":"the chances of your brain learning how to see"},{"time":82000,"text":"are very, very slim --"},{"time":84000,"text":"again, slim or none."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"So when I heard these two things,"},{"time":89000,"text":"it troubled me deeply,"},{"time":91000,"text":"both because of personal reasons"},{"time":93000,"text":"and scientific reasons."},{"time":95000,"text":"So let me first start with the personal reason."},{"time":98000,"text":"It'll sound corny, but it's sincere."},{"time":101000,"text":"That's my son, Darius."},{"time":103000,"text":"As a new father,"},{"time":105000,"text":"I have a qualitatively different sense"},{"time":109000,"text":"of just how delicate babies are,"},{"time":112000,"text":"what our obligations are towards them"},{"time":115000,"text":"and how much love"},{"time":117000,"text":"we can feel towards a child."},{"time":120000,"text":"I would move heaven and earth"},{"time":122000,"text":"in order to get treatment for Darius,"},{"time":125000,"text":"and for me to be told"},{"time":127000,"text":"that there might be other Dariuses"},{"time":129000,"text":"who are not getting treatment,"},{"time":131000,"text":"that's just viscerally wrong."},{"time":134000,"text":"So that's the personal reason."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136000,"text":"Scientific reason is that this notion"},{"time":139000,"text":"from neuroscience of critical periods --"},{"time":141000,"text":"that if the brain is older"},{"time":144000,"text":"than four or five years of age,"},{"time":146000,"text":"it loses its ability to learn --"},{"time":148000,"text":"that doesn't sit well with me,"},{"time":150000,"text":"because I don't think that idea"},{"time":152000,"text":"has been tested adequately."},{"time":155000,"text":"The birth of the idea is from"},{"time":157000,"text":"David Hubel and Torsten Wiesel's work,"},{"time":159000,"text":"two researchers who were at Harvard,"},{"time":161000,"text":"and they got the Nobel Prize in 1981"},{"time":164000,"text":"for their studies of visual physiology,"},{"time":166000,"text":"which are remarkably beautiful studies,"},{"time":168000,"text":"but I believe some of their work"},{"time":170000,"text":"has been extrapolated"},{"time":172000,"text":"into the human domain prematurely."},{"time":174000,"text":"So, they did their work with kittens,"},{"time":176000,"text":"with different kinds of deprivation regiments,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and those studies,"},{"time":180000,"text":"which date back to the '60s,"},{"time":182000,"text":"are now being applied to human children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"So I felt that I needed to do two things."},{"time":188000,"text":"One: provide care"},{"time":191000,"text":"to children who are currently"},{"time":193000,"text":"being deprived of treatment."},{"time":195000,"text":"That's the humanitarian mission."},{"time":197000,"text":"And the scientific mission would be"},{"time":199000,"text":"to test the limits"},{"time":201000,"text":"of visual plasticity."},{"time":203000,"text":"And these two missions, as you can tell,"},{"time":206000,"text":"thread together perfectly. One adds to the other;"},{"time":209000,"text":"in fact, one would be impossible without the other."},{"time":214000,"text":"So, to implement"},{"time":216000,"text":"these twin missions,"},{"time":218000,"text":"a few years ago, I launched Project Prakash."},{"time":221000,"text":"Prakash, as many of you know,"},{"time":223000,"text":"is the Sanskrit word for light,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and the idea is that"},{"time":227000,"text":"in bringing light into the lives of children,"},{"time":230000,"text":"we also have a chance"},{"time":232000,"text":"of shedding light on some of the"},{"time":234000,"text":"deepest mysteries of neuroscience."},{"time":237000,"text":"And the logo -- even though it looks extremely Irish,"},{"time":240000,"text":"it's actually derived from"},{"time":242000,"text":"the Indian symbol of Diya, an earthen lamp."},{"time":246000,"text":"The Prakash, the overall effort"},{"time":249000,"text":"has three components:"},{"time":251000,"text":"outreach, to identify children in need of care;"},{"time":255000,"text":"medical treatment; and in subsequent study."},{"time":258000,"text":"And I want to show you a short video clip"},{"time":261000,"text":"that illustrates the first two components of this work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"This is an outreach station"},{"time":268000,"text":"conducted at a school for the blind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271000,"text":"(Text: Most of the children are profoundly and permanently blind ...)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":276000,"text":"Pawan Sinha: So, because this is a school for the blind,"},{"time":281000,"text":"many children have permanent conditions."},{"time":283000,"text":"That's a case of microphthalmos,"},{"time":286000,"text":"which is malformed eyes,"},{"time":288000,"text":"and that's a permanent condition;"},{"time":290000,"text":"it cannot be treated."},{"time":292000,"text":"That's an extreme of micropthalmos"},{"time":294000,"text":"called enophthalmos."},{"time":296000,"text":"But, every so often, we come across children"},{"time":298000,"text":"who show some residual vision,"},{"time":301000,"text":"and that is a very good sign"},{"time":304000,"text":"that the condition might actually be treatable."},{"time":306000,"text":"So, after that screening, we bring the children to the hospital."},{"time":309000,"text":"That's the hospital we're working with in Delhi,"},{"time":311000,"text":"the Schroff Charity Eye Hospital."},{"time":314000,"text":"It has a very well-equipped"},{"time":316000,"text":"pediatric ophthalmic center,"},{"time":320000,"text":"which was made possible in part"},{"time":322000,"text":"by a gift from the Ronald McDonald charity."},{"time":326000,"text":"So, eating burgers actually helps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330000,"text":"(Text: Such examinations allow us to improve"},{"time":332000,"text":"eye-health in many children, and ..."},{"time":339000,"text":"... help us find children who can participate in Project Prakash.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"PS: So, as I zoom in to the eyes of this child,"},{"time":344000,"text":"you will see the cause of his blindness."},{"time":348000,"text":"The whites that you see in the middle of his pupils"},{"time":351000,"text":"are congenital cataracts,"},{"time":354000,"text":"so opacities of the lens."},{"time":356000,"text":"In our eyes, the lens is clear,"},{"time":359000,"text":"but in this child, the lens has become opaque,"},{"time":361000,"text":"and therefore he can't see the world."},{"time":364000,"text":"So, the child is given treatment. You'll see shots of the eye."},{"time":367000,"text":"Here's the eye with the opaque lens,"},{"time":369000,"text":"the opaque lens extracted"},{"time":371000,"text":"and an acrylic lens inserted."},{"time":374000,"text":"And here's the same child"},{"time":376000,"text":"three weeks post-operation,"},{"time":379000,"text":"with the right eye open."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393000,"text":"So, even from that little clip, you can begin to get the sense"},{"time":396000,"text":"that recovery is possible,"},{"time":398000,"text":"and we have now"},{"time":400000,"text":"provided treatment to over 200 children,"},{"time":403000,"text":"and the story repeats itself."},{"time":405000,"text":"After treatment, the child"},{"time":407000,"text":"gains significant functionality."},{"time":410000,"text":"In fact, the story holds true"},{"time":413000,"text":"even if you have a person who got sight"},{"time":415000,"text":"after several years of deprivation."},{"time":417000,"text":"We did a paper a few years ago"},{"time":419000,"text":"about this woman that you see on the right, SRD,"},{"time":423000,"text":"and she got her sight late in life,"},{"time":425000,"text":"and her vision is remarkable at this age."},{"time":429000,"text":"I should add a tragic postscript to this --"},{"time":432000,"text":"she died two years ago"},{"time":434000,"text":"in a bus accident."},{"time":436000,"text":"So, hers is just a truly inspiring story --"},{"time":440000,"text":"unknown, but inspiring story."},{"time":443000,"text":"So when we started finding these results,"},{"time":445000,"text":"as you might imagine, it created quite a bit of stir"},{"time":448000,"text":"in the scientific and the popular press."},{"time":451000,"text":"Here's an article in Nature"},{"time":453000,"text":"that profiled this work,"},{"time":455000,"text":"and another one in Time."},{"time":457000,"text":"So, we were fairly convinced -- we are convinced --"},{"time":459000,"text":"that recovery is feasible,"},{"time":461000,"text":"despite extended visual deprivation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"The next obvious question to ask:"},{"time":466000,"text":"What is the process of recovery?"},{"time":469000,"text":"So, the way we study that is,"},{"time":472000,"text":"let's say we find a child who has light sensitivity."},{"time":474000,"text":"The child is provided treatment,"},{"time":476000,"text":"and I want to stress that the treatment"},{"time":478000,"text":"is completely unconditional;"},{"time":480000,"text":"there is no quid pro quo."},{"time":482000,"text":"We treat many more children then we actually work with."},{"time":485000,"text":"Every child who needs treatment is treated."},{"time":488000,"text":"After treatment, about every week,"},{"time":490000,"text":"we run the child"},{"time":492000,"text":"on a battery of simple visual tests"},{"time":495000,"text":"in order to see how their visual skills"},{"time":497000,"text":"are coming on line."},{"time":499000,"text":"And we try to do this for as long as possible."},{"time":502000,"text":"This arc of development"},{"time":504000,"text":"gives us unprecedented"},{"time":506000,"text":"and extremely valuable information"},{"time":508000,"text":"about how the scaffolding of vision"},{"time":510000,"text":"gets set up."},{"time":512000,"text":"What might be the causal connections"},{"time":514000,"text":"between the early developing skills"},{"time":516000,"text":"and the later developing ones?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":518000,"text":"And we've used this general approach to study"},{"time":520000,"text":"many different visual proficiencies,"},{"time":523000,"text":"but I want to highlight one particular one,"},{"time":527000,"text":"and that is image parsing into objects."},{"time":530000,"text":"So, any image of the kind that you see on the left,"},{"time":532000,"text":"be it a real image or a synthetic image,"},{"time":535000,"text":"it's made up of little regions"},{"time":537000,"text":"that you see in the middle column,"},{"time":539000,"text":"regions of different colors, different luminances."},{"time":542000,"text":"The brain has this complex task"},{"time":545000,"text":"of putting together, integrating,"},{"time":548000,"text":"subsets of these regions"},{"time":550000,"text":"into something that's more meaningful,"},{"time":552000,"text":"into what we would consider to be objects,"},{"time":554000,"text":"as you see on the right."},{"time":556000,"text":"And nobody knows how this integration happens,"},{"time":558000,"text":"and that's the question we asked with Project Prakash."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562000,"text":"So, here's what happens"},{"time":564000,"text":"very soon after the onset of sight."},{"time":567000,"text":"Here's a person who had gained sight just a couple of weeks ago,"},{"time":570000,"text":"and you see Ethan Myers, a graduate student from MIT,"},{"time":573000,"text":"running the experiment with him."},{"time":576000,"text":"His visual-motor coordination is quite poor,"},{"time":580000,"text":"but you get a general sense"},{"time":582000,"text":"of what are the regions that he's trying to trace out."},{"time":585000,"text":"If you show him real world images,"},{"time":587000,"text":"if you show others like him real world images,"},{"time":590000,"text":"they are unable to recognize most of the objects"},{"time":592000,"text":"because the world to them is over-fragmented;"},{"time":595000,"text":"it's made up of a collage, a patchwork,"},{"time":598000,"text":"of regions of different colors and luminances."},{"time":600000,"text":"And that's what's indicated in the green outlines."},{"time":602000,"text":"When you ask them,"},{"time":604000,"text":"\"Even if you can't name the objects, just point to where the objects are,\""},{"time":607000,"text":"these are the regions that they point to."},{"time":609000,"text":"So the world is this complex"},{"time":611000,"text":"patchwork of regions."},{"time":613000,"text":"Even the shadow on the ball"},{"time":615000,"text":"becomes its own object."},{"time":618000,"text":"Interestingly enough,"},{"time":620000,"text":"you give them a few months,"},{"time":622000,"text":"and this is what happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"Doctor: How many are these?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"Patient: These are two things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632000,"text":"Doctor: What are their shapes?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":634000,"text":"Patient: Their shapes ..."},{"time":636000,"text":"This one is a circle,"},{"time":639000,"text":"and this"},{"time":641000,"text":"is a square."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643000,"text":"PS: A very dramatic transformation has come about."},{"time":646000,"text":"And the question is:"},{"time":648000,"text":"What underlies this transformation?"},{"time":650000,"text":"It's a profound question,"},{"time":652000,"text":"and what's even more amazing is how simple"},{"time":654000,"text":"the answer is."},{"time":656000,"text":"The answer lies in motion"},{"time":658000,"text":"and that's what I want to show you in the next clip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"Doctor: What shape do you see here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"Patient: I can't make it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673000,"text":"Doctor: Now?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":676000,"text":"Patient: Triangle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680000,"text":"Doctor: How many things are these?"},{"time":693000,"text":"Now, how many things are these?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":696000,"text":"Patient: Two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698000,"text":"Doctor: What are these things?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":701000,"text":"Patient: A square and a circle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703000,"text":"PS: And we see this pattern over and over again."},{"time":706000,"text":"The one thing the visual system needs"},{"time":709000,"text":"in order to begin parsing the world"},{"time":711000,"text":"is dynamic information."},{"time":713000,"text":"So the inference we are deriving from this,"},{"time":715000,"text":"and several such experiments,"},{"time":717000,"text":"is that dynamic information processing,"},{"time":719000,"text":"or motion processing,"},{"time":721000,"text":"serves as the bedrock for building"},{"time":723000,"text":"the rest of the complexity of visual processing;"},{"time":727000,"text":"it leads to visual integration"},{"time":729000,"text":"and eventually to recognition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732000,"text":"This simple idea has far reaching implications."},{"time":735000,"text":"And let me just quickly mention two,"},{"time":738000,"text":"one, drawing from the domain of engineering,"},{"time":740000,"text":"and one from the clinic."},{"time":742000,"text":"So, from the perspective of engineering,"},{"time":744000,"text":"we can ask: Goven that we know"},{"time":747000,"text":"that motion is so important for the human visual system,"},{"time":749000,"text":"can we use this as a recipe"},{"time":752000,"text":"for constructing machine-based vision systems"},{"time":755000,"text":"that can learn on their own, that don't need to be programmed"},{"time":758000,"text":"by a human programmer?"},{"time":760000,"text":"And that's what we're trying to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762000,"text":"I'm at MIT, at MIT you need to apply"},{"time":765000,"text":"whatever basic knowledge you gain."},{"time":767000,"text":"So we are creating Dylan,"},{"time":769000,"text":"which is a computational system"},{"time":771000,"text":"with an ambitious goal"},{"time":773000,"text":"of taking in visual inputs"},{"time":775000,"text":"of the same kind that a human child would receive,"},{"time":778000,"text":"and autonomously discovering:"},{"time":780000,"text":"What are the objects in this visual input?"},{"time":783000,"text":"So, don't worry about the internals of Dylan."},{"time":786000,"text":"Here, I'm just going to talk about"},{"time":789000,"text":"how we test Dylan."},{"time":791000,"text":"The way we test Dylan is by giving it"},{"time":793000,"text":"inputs, as I said, of the same kind"},{"time":796000,"text":"that a baby, or a child in Project Prakash would get."},{"time":799000,"text":"But for a long time we couldn't quite figure out:"},{"time":802000,"text":"Wow can we get these kinds of video inputs?"},{"time":806000,"text":"So, I thought,"},{"time":808000,"text":"could we have Darius"},{"time":810000,"text":"serve as our babycam carrier,"},{"time":813000,"text":"and that way get the inputs that we feed into Dylan?"},{"time":816000,"text":"So that's what we did."},{"time":818000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":825000,"text":"I had to have long conversations with my wife."},{"time":828000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":833000,"text":"In fact, Pam, if you're watching this,"},{"time":835000,"text":"please forgive me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838000,"text":"So, we modified the optics of the camera"},{"time":842000,"text":"in order to mimic the baby's visual acuity."},{"time":845000,"text":"As some of you might know,"},{"time":847000,"text":"babyies are born pretty much legally blind."},{"time":851000,"text":"Their acuity -- our acuity is 20/20;"},{"time":854000,"text":"babies' acuity is like 20/800,"},{"time":857000,"text":"so they are looking at the world"},{"time":859000,"text":"in a very, very blurry fashion."},{"time":862000,"text":"Here's what a baby-cam video looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":875000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":878000,"text":"Thankfully, there isn't any audio"},{"time":880000,"text":"to go with this."},{"time":883000,"text":"What's amazing is that working with such"},{"time":885000,"text":"highly degraded input,"},{"time":887000,"text":"the baby, very quickly, is able"},{"time":889000,"text":"to discover meaning in such input."},{"time":892000,"text":"But then two or three days afterward,"},{"time":894000,"text":"babies begin to pay attention"},{"time":896000,"text":"to their mother's or their father's face."},{"time":898000,"text":"How does that happen? We want Dylan to be able to do that,"},{"time":901000,"text":"and using this mantra of motion,"},{"time":904000,"text":"Dylan actually can do that."},{"time":906000,"text":"So, given that kind of video input,"},{"time":909000,"text":"with just about six or seven minutes worth of video,"},{"time":912000,"text":"Dylan can begin to extract patterns"},{"time":915000,"text":"that include faces."},{"time":918000,"text":"So, it's an important demonstration"},{"time":920000,"text":"of the power of motion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"The clinical implication, it comes from the domain of autism."},{"time":925000,"text":"Visual integration has been associated with autism"},{"time":927000,"text":"by several researchers."},{"time":929000,"text":"When we saw that, we asked:"},{"time":931000,"text":"Could the impairment in visual integration"},{"time":934000,"text":"be the manifestation of something underneath,"},{"time":937000,"text":"of dynamic information processing deficiencies in autism?"},{"time":940000,"text":"Because, if that hypothesis were to be true,"},{"time":943000,"text":"it would have massive repercussions in our understanding"},{"time":946000,"text":"of what's causing the many different aspects"},{"time":948000,"text":"of the autism phenotype."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951000,"text":"What you're going to see are"},{"time":953000,"text":"video clips of two children -- one neurotypical,"},{"time":956000,"text":"one with autism, playing Pong."},{"time":958000,"text":"So, while the child is playing Pong, we are tracking where they're looking."},{"time":961000,"text":"In red are the eye movement traces."},{"time":964000,"text":"This is the neurotypical child, and what you see"},{"time":967000,"text":"is that the child is able to make cues"},{"time":969000,"text":"of the dynamic information"},{"time":971000,"text":"to predict where the ball is going to go."},{"time":973000,"text":"Even before the ball gets to a place,"},{"time":976000,"text":"the child is already looking there."},{"time":979000,"text":"Contrast this with a child"},{"time":981000,"text":"with autism playing the same game."},{"time":983000,"text":"Instead of anticipating,"},{"time":985000,"text":"the child always follows where the ball has been."},{"time":988000,"text":"The efficiency of the use"},{"time":990000,"text":"of dynamic information"},{"time":992000,"text":"seems to be significantly compromised in autism."},{"time":996000,"text":"So we are pursuing this line of work"},{"time":999000,"text":"and hopefully we'll have"},{"time":1001000,"text":"more results to report soon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1003000,"text":"Looking ahead, if you think of this disk"},{"time":1006000,"text":"as representing all of the children"},{"time":1008000,"text":"we've treated so far,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"this is the magnitude of the problem."},{"time":1012000,"text":"The red dots are the children we have not treated."},{"time":1015000,"text":"So, there are many, many more children who need to be treated,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"and in order to expand the scope of the project,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"we are planning on launching"},{"time":1022000,"text":"The Prakash Center for Children,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"which will have a dedicated pediatric hospital,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"a school for the children we are treating"},{"time":1029000,"text":"and also a cutting-edge research facility."},{"time":1031000,"text":"The Prakash Center will integrate health care,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"education and research in a way"},{"time":1036000,"text":"that truly creates the whole"},{"time":1038000,"text":"to be greater than the sum of the parts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041000,"text":"So, to summarize: Prakash, in its five years of existence,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"it's had an impact in multiple areas,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"ranging from basic neuroscience"},{"time":1049000,"text":"plasticity and learning in the brain,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"to clinically relevant hypotheses like in autism,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"the development of autonomous machine vision systems,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"education of the undergraduate and graduate students,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"and most importantly in the alleviation"},{"time":1063000,"text":"of childhood blindness."},{"time":1065000,"text":"And for my students and I, it's been"},{"time":1067000,"text":"just a phenomenal experience"},{"time":1069000,"text":"because we have gotten to do interesting research,"},{"time":1073000,"text":"while at the same time"},{"time":1075000,"text":"helping the many children that we have worked with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}